4. SOFTWARE ECOSYSTEM: VAULTOS

4.1 Kernel Architecture

```
Base: seL4 formally verified microkernel
Security: Capability-based access control
Size: 50,000 lines of verified code
Boot Time: < 100ms from cold start
Update Mechanism: A/B partitions with rollback protection
```

4.2 File System: Quantum-Safe Encrypted File System (QSEFS)

```
Features:
- Per-file encryption with metadata protection
- Deniable encryption (plausible deniability modes)
- Versioning with infinite undo capability
- Cross-drive synchronization with CRDTs
- Automatic format migration (10-year cycles)

Performance:
- Latency: 10 μs for 4K random read
- Throughput: 10 GB/s sustained sequential
- IOPS: 2M random 4K read, 1M write
```

4.3 Management Interface

```
API Layers:
1. Low-level: Rust/C API for embedded systems
2. Middle: gRPC/protobuf for enterprise integration
3. High-level: Natural language via Trinity AI
4. Emergency: Morse code via LED (no power required)

Management Platforms:
- Web UI: Zero-knowledge administration portal
- Mobile: iOS/Android with biometric access
- CLI: Linux/macOS/Windows terminal
- Enterprise: Kubernetes CSI driver, VMware plugin
```

