Assembly:
- Flex: High-reliability electronics assembly
- Sanmina: Military/aerospace-grade testing
- CATL: Solid-state battery manufacturing
```

5.2 Production Flow

```
Phase 1: Component Fabrication (12 weeks)
  Week 1-4: Silica storage medium patterning
  Week 5-8: SoC wafer fabrication and testing
  Week 9-10: Composite shield manufacturing
  Week 11-12: Battery and optical assembly

Phase 2: Integration (4 weeks)
  Week 13: Die stacking and interposer attachment
  Week 14: Enclosure assembly and hermetic sealing
  Week 15: Firmware burn-in and calibration
  Week 16: Final testing and certification

Yield Management:
- Target: 85% final yield
- Cost: $450/unit at 10k/month volume
- Scalability: Linear scaling to 100k/month
```

5.3 Quality Assurance

```
Testing Regimen:
1. Burn-in: 168 hours at 85°C with full I/O load
2. Environmental: MIL-STD-810H, 50 cycles each
3. Security: FIPS 140-3 Level 4 validation suite
4. Longevity: Accelerated aging equivalent to 50 years
5. Radiation: NASA SEE testing protocol

Certifications:
- ISO 9001:2015 (Quality Management)
- ISO 27001 (Information Security)
- UL 1642 (Battery Safety)
- FCC/CE/RoHS (Global Market Access)
